===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|recipiō||receive|lang=la}}. Compare {{term|receipt}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɹɛs.ɪ.pi/|/ˈɹɛs.ə.pi/}}
* {{audio|En-us-recipe.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|medicine|archaic|lang=en}} A [[formula]] for preparing or using a [[medicine]]; a [[prescription]]; also, a medicine prepared from such instructions. {{defdate|from 16th c.}}
# Any set of [[instruction]]s for preparing a mixture of ingredients. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}
# By extension, a [[plan]] or procedure to obtain a given end result. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}
#: ''His new approach is definitely a '''recipe''' for success.''
# Now especially, a set of instructions for making or preparing [[food]] dishes. {{defdate|from 18th c.}}

